<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1437447-did-anyone-else-get-deep-into-this-and">Did anyone else get deep into this and just not care? For me, the writing is solid and you enter the world he creates pretty easily, but something is missing. I know lots of lit fiction has that feel, but this novel, for me at least, didn&#39;t have you waiting for/wanting something enough. Instead of a story, I feel like we got a biography about the every-day life of regular people whose lives aren&#39;t that interesting.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1437447'><a id="like_count_community_question_1437447" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1437447?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F107821.Bridge_of_Sighs">like</a></span>

</li>
