<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/77920572-stan-blackburn"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1622890051i/77920572._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/77920572-stan-blackburn">Stan Blackburn</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Like Sarah&apos;s painting, &apos;Bridge of Sighs&apos; is a view of the complexity of a life well (and imperfectly) lived. There are so many deep themes in this wor<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Like Sarah's painting, 'Bridge of Sighs' is a view of the complexity of a life well (and imperfectly) lived. There are so many deep themes in this work. The story, however, has nothing to do with plot. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
