    <a title="Julie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1213607-julie"><img alt="Julie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612145096p2/1213607.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/24840781?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julie" href="/user/show/1213607-julie">Julie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1213607-julie?shelf=contemporary-fiction">contemporary-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1213607-julie?shelf=usa-contemporary">usa-contemporary</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer24840781" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13095257651496763529">Reading this book is like slipping on your favorite pair of jeans- the ones you never wash to keep them perfect softly and loose, donning a beloved sweatshirt and thinking &quot;I wish I lived the sort of life that I could wear these clothes every day...&quot; Meaning that (if you like Russo, of course) these characters, this setting, the storyline are so comforting and familiar- it&apos;s like coming home.<br/><br/>Which isn&apos;t to say that there aren&apos;t surprises, that it isn&apos;t fresh, nuanced and captivating. It&apos;s a been</span>
  <span id="freeText13095257651496763529" style="display:none">Reading this book is like slipping on your favorite pair of jeans- the ones you never wash to keep them perfect softly and loose, donning a beloved sweatshirt and thinking "I wish I lived the sort of life that I could wear these clothes every day..." Meaning that (if you like Russo, of course) these characters, this setting, the storyline are so comforting and familiar- it's like coming home.<br /><br />Which isn't to say that there aren't surprises, that it isn't fresh, nuanced and captivating. It's a been a definite page turner for me- only work and the other vagaries of life have kept me from finishing it over the weekend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13095257651496763529" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
